Defendant Zachariah A Fox in court with attorney Mark E. Kershek.  Ted S. Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is trying to raise money for restitution prior to sentencing.  Case recalled at 4:10.  Parties are ready to proceed with sentencing.  Recommendations by the State.  Arguments by the Defense.  Statement by defendant's mother.  Statement by defendant.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
9 months jail.  First 90 days straight time, balance with HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS. (Credit - 0 days)

Term of Probation: 1 Year
Conditions of Probation:
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
-	Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
-	Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-	Sign Medical Release for Agent;
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
-	No contact with any Kohls Store in Waukesha County.
Restitution: paid
Costs: $ 253.00
(To to be paid at the rate of $50.00  per month commencing 10/1/15).

Condition Time: 30 days NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - Last 20 days STAYED for use by Agent.
